	~	MWh/MWh / (MWh/t) = t/MWh 
		t/MWh * 1000 = kg/MWh
		kg/MWh / 3.6 = kg/GJ
	|

international aviation BioKero hydrogen demand=
	BioKero IA * HVO Kerosene H2 cost scaler * 3.6
	~	t H2
	~	Convert from GWh jetfuel to GWh G2 - then to MWh H2 - then to tons H2
	|

HtJ Fuel Gas cost recovery fraction=
	(Grey NG cost * HtJ fuel gas fraction) /
	(Grey NG cost * HtJ fuel gas fraction + 
	Jetfuel cost * HtJ Kerosene fraction + 
	Naphtha cost * HtJ Naphtha fraction)
	~	
	~	20% of the costs are assumed covered by the sale of naphtha.
	|

HD innovator pipeline=
	HD continuous investment / (1-innovators) * innovators
	~	MT NH3
	~		|

HtJ Kerosene cost recovery fraction=
	(Jetfuel cost * HtJ Kerosene fraction) /
	(Grey NG cost * HtJ fuel gas fraction + 
	Jetfuel cost * HtJ Kerosene fraction + 
	Naphtha cost * HtJ Naphtha fraction)
	~	
	~	80% of the total costs are covered by the revenues generated by kerosene \
		sale.
	|

HtJ Kerosene cost wo H2=
	HtJ process cost wo H2 * HtJ Kerosene cost recovery fraction / (HtJ Kerosene fraction\
		 * HtJ liquid output)
	~	€/GJ
	~		|

international aviation SynKero hydrogen demand=
	SynKero IA * HtJ Kerosene H2 cost scaler * 3.6
	~	t H2
	~	Convert from GWh jetfuel to GWh G2 - then to MWh H2 - then to tons H2
	|

HtJ Kerosene H2 cost scaler=
	HtJ H2 Usage * HtJ Kerosene cost recovery fraction / H2 LHV * 1000 / 3.6 / HtJ liquid output\
		 / HtJ Kerosene fraction
	~	kg/GJ
	~	MWh/MWh / (MWh/t) = t/MWh 
		t/MWh * 1000 = kg/MWh
		kg/MWh / 3.6 = kg/GJ
	|

BioNaphtha Cost as HVO byproduct=
	BioDiesel Cost / 0.95 * 0.05 / HVO Jet Naphtha fraction
	~	€/GJ
	~		|

LD innovator pipeline=
	LD continuous investment/ (1-innovators) * innovators
	~	GWh
	~		|

HtJ process cost wo H2=
	PS CC cost/CC Capture Rate * HtJ CO2 usage  / HtJ liquids LHV / HtJ liquid output - \
		HEAT COST  * HtJ Excess Heat / 3.6 
	+ 
	(HtJ AF * HtJ CAPEX / HtJ operating hours + HtJ OPEX + HtJ variable) / HtJ liquid output\
		 / 3.6
	~	€/GJ input
	~		|

IA innovator pipeline=
	IA continuous investment / (1-innovators) * innovators
	~	GWh
	~		|

steel innovator pipeline=
	steel continuous investment / (1-innovators) * innovators
	~	MT steel
	~		|

naphtha innovator pipeline=
	naphtha continuous investment / (1-innovators) * innovators
	~	MT naphtha
	~		|

HtJ liquids LHV=
	HtJ fuel gas fraction * Methane LHV + HtJ Kerosene fraction * Jetfuel LHV + HtJ Naphtha fraction\
		 * Naphtha LHV
	~	GJ/t
	~		|

HtJ Naphtha cost recovery fraction=
	(Naphtha cost * HtJ Naphtha fraction) /
	(Grey NG cost * HtJ fuel gas fraction + 
	Jetfuel cost * HtJ Kerosene fraction + 
	Naphtha cost * HtJ Naphtha fraction)
	~	
	~	20% of the costs are assumed covered by the sale of naphtha.
	|

HtJ Naphtha cost wo H2=
	HtJ process cost wo H2 * HtJ Naphtha cost recovery fraction / (HtJ Naphtha fraction \
		* HtJ liquid output)
	~	€/GJ
	~		|

HVO Jet Naphtha fraction=0.483486
	~	percent
	~	Percent of liquid fuels which is naphtha
	|

MeOH innovator pipeline=
	MeOH continuous investment / (1-innovators) * innovators
	~	MT MeOH
	~		|

domestic aviation BioKero hydrogen demand=
	BioKero DA * HVO Kerosene H2 cost scaler * 3.6
	~	t H2
	~	Convert from GWh to GJ, then from GJ to tons fuel, then from tons fuel to tons H2.
		Example 1:
		MeOH cons. [GWh] * 3600 [GJ/GWh] / 19.9 [GJ/t] / 15.7 [t MeOH/t H2]
		Example 2:
		NH3 cons. [GWh] * 3600 [GJ/GWh] / 18.6 [GJ/t] / 5.56 [t NH3/t H2]
	|

DS innovator pipeline=
	DS continuous investment / (1-innovators) * innovators
	~	GWh
	~		|

HVO Jet Naphtha cost recovery fraction=
	(Naphtha cost * HVO Jet Naphtha fraction) /
	(Grey NG cost * (HVO Jet LPG fraction + HVO Jet Fuel Gas fraction) + 
	Jetfuel cost * HVO Jet Kerosene fraction + 
	Naphtha cost * HVO Jet Naphtha fraction)
	~	
	~	7% of the costs are assumed covered by the sale of naphtha.
	|

domestic aviation SynKero hydrogen demand=
	SynKero DA * HtJ Kerosene H2 cost scaler * 3.6
	~	t H2
	~	Convert from GWh to GJ, then from GJ to tons fuel, then from tons fuel to tons H2.
		Example 1:
		MeOH cons. [GWh] * 3600 [GJ/GWh] / 19.9 [GJ/t] / 15.7 [t MeOH/t H2]
		Example 2:
		NH3 cons. [GWh] * 3600 [GJ/GWh] / 18.6 [GJ/t] / 5.56 [t NH3/t H2]
	|

HVO Jet Fuel Gas cost recovery fraction=
	(Grey NG cost * (HVO Jet Fuel Gas fraction + HVO Jet LPG fraction)) /
	(Grey NG cost * (HVO Jet Fuel Gas fraction + HVO Jet LPG fraction) + 
	Jetfuel cost * HVO Jet Kerosene fraction + 
	Naphtha cost * HVO Jet Naphtha fraction)
	~	
	~	20% of the costs are assumed covered by the sale of naphtha.
	|

HVO Jet Kerosene cost recovery fraction=
	(Jetfuel cost * HVO Jet Kerosene fraction) /
	(Grey NG cost * (HVO Jet Fuel Gas fraction + HVO Jet LPG fraction) + 
	Jetfuel cost * HVO Jet Kerosene fraction + 
	Naphtha cost * HVO Jet Naphtha fraction)
	~	
	~	80% of the total costs are covered by the revenues generated by kerosene \
		sale.
	|

HtJ Naphtha H2 cost scaler=
	HtJ H2 Usage * HtJ Naphtha cost recovery fraction / H2 LHV * 1000 / 3.6 / HtJ liquid output\
		 / HtJ Naphtha fraction
	~	kg/GJ
	~	MWh/MWh / (MWh/t) = t/MWh 
		t/MWh * 1000 = kg/MWh
		kg/MWh / 3.6 = kg/GJ
	|

DA innovator pipeline=
	DA continuous investment / (1-innovators) * innovators
	~	MT NH3
	~		|

HVO Kerosene cost wo H2=
	HVO process cost wo H2 * HVO Jet Kerosene cost recovery fraction / HVO Jet Kerosene fraction
	~	€/GJ
	~		|

fertilizer innovator pipeline=
	fertilizer continuous investment / (1-innovators) * innovators
	~	MT NH3
	~		|

IS innovator pipeline=
	IS continuous investment / (1-innovators) * innovators
	~	GWh
	~		|

SynNaphtha H2 subsidy limit=
	10^9
	~	M€
	~		|

SynKero cost=
	HtJ Kerosene cost wo H2 + SynKero H2 cost * HtJ Kerosene H2 cost scaler
	~	€/GJ
	~	Carbon cost in €/MWh output assuming all outputs LHV is equal to jetfuel's.
		The additional variable costs in €/MWh output using SynKero Output as the \
		efficiency of the process. Here the potential heat sale is also subtracted.
		Then the annualized capex is added in €/MWh and fixed + variable OPEX in the same \
		unit.
		
		Finally it is all divided by the jetfuel fraction, which assumes that 60% \
		of the output is jetfuel. This price in €/MWh is then multiplied by 0.8, \
		which assumes that sale of byproducts in the form of gasoline (20%) and \
		LPG (20%) can bring in further cost reductions. 3600 is the conversion \
		from MWh to MJ.
	|

BioKero H2 subsidy=
	IF THEN ELSE(
	  (domestic aviation subsidy YTD+international aviation subsidy YTD)
	    < BioKero H2 subsidy limit,
	  PULSE( 2025, BioKero H2 subsidy length) * BioKero H2 subsidy size,
	  0
	)
	~	€/kg
	~		|

SynKero H2 WTP=
	(Jetfuel cost - HtJ Kerosene cost wo H2) / HtJ Kerosene H2 cost scaler
	~	€/kg
	~		|

BioNaphtha cost=
	HVO Naphtha cost wo H2 + BioNaphtha H2 cost * HVO Naphtha H2 cost scaler
	~	€/GJ
	~	The naphtha coproduct sale cover 7.5% of the production costs.
		The LPG coproduct sale cover the remaining 2.5% of the production costs.
		Note here is that the naphtha output is quite low, which does not motivate \
		this as the primary method to produce biogenic naphtha.
	|

SynKero H2 actual subsidy=
	Green H2 cost - SynKero H2 cost
	~	€/kg
	~		|

SynKero H2 subsidy=
	IF THEN ELSE(
	  (domestic aviation subsidy YTD+international aviation subsidy YTD)
	    < SynKero H2 subsidy limit,
	  PULSE( 2025, SynKero H2 subsidy length) * SynKero H2 subsidy size,
	  0
	)
	~	€/kg
	~		|

SynKero H2 subsidy length=
	10
	~	years
	~		|

SynKero H2 subsidy limit=
	10^9
	~	M€
	~		|

SynNaphtha cost=
	HtJ Naphtha cost wo H2 + SynNaphtha H2 cost * HtJ Naphtha H2 cost scaler
	~	€/GJ
	~	Assume that 80 % of the costs are covered by the jetfuel revenue (jetfuel \
		is 60% of the output) - then assume that 30 % of the output is suitable as \
		naphtha and sell that, covering the 20% remaining costs.
	|

high temperature innovator pipeline=
	high temperature continuous investment / (1-innovators) * innovators
	~	GWh
	~		|

SynNaphtha H2 WTP=
	(Naphtha cost - HtJ Naphtha cost wo H2) / HtJ Naphtha H2 cost scaler
	~	€/kgH2
	~		|

BioNaphtha H2 actual subsidy=
	Green H2 cost - BioNaphtha H2 cost
	~	€/kg
	~		|

SynNaphtha H2 subsidy=
	IF THEN ELSE(
	  naphtha subsidy YTD
	    < SynNaphtha H2 subsidy limit,
	  PULSE( 2025, SynNaphtha H2 subsidy length) * SynNaphtha H2 subsidy size,
	  0
	)
	~	€/kgH2
	~		|

BioNaphtha H2 subsidy=
	IF THEN ELSE(
	 naphtha subsidy YTD
	    < BioNaphtha H2 subsidy limit,
	  PULSE( 2025, BioNaphtha H2 subsidy length) * BioNaphtha H2 subsidy size,
	  0
	)
	~	€/kgH2
	~		|

SynNaphtha H2 actual subsidy=
	Green H2 cost - SynNaphtha H2 cost
	~	€/kg
	~		|

BioNaphtha H2 subsidy limit=
	10^9
	~	M€
	~		|

HtJ CAPEX = WITH LOOKUP (
	Time,
		( [(0,0)-(10,10)], (2019, 2.1e+06), (2030, 1.6e+06), (2040, 1.1e+06), (2050, 900000\
		)))
	~	€/MWfuel
	~		|

HtJ variable = WITH LOOKUP (
	Time,
		( [(0,0)-(10,10)], (2019, 5.3 ), (2030, 4.2 ), (2040, 3.2 ), (2050, 2.1 )))
	~	€/MWh
	~	€/MWh of liquids/fuels
	|

HVO Jet Fuel Gas fraction=0
	~	MWh/MWh input
	~		|

HtJ fuel gas fraction=
	1 - HtJ Kerosene fraction - HtJ Naphtha fraction
	~	percent
	~	Percent of liquid fuels which is jetfuel
	|

BioKero H2 WTP=
	(Jetfuel cost - HVO Kerosene cost wo H2) / HVO Kerosene H2 cost scaler
	~	€/kg
	~		|

HtJ Naphtha fraction=
	(1 - HtJ Kerosene fraction) * 0.75
	~	percent
	~	Assumes that 75% of the remaining Fischer Tropsch liquids can be used as \
		naphtha. If the kerosene fraction is 60% (base assumption) then this \
		leaves 10 % of FT liquids as byproducts which are probably light products \
		(LPG/fuel gas).
	|

BioKero cost=
	HVO Kerosene cost wo H2 + HVO Kerosene H2 cost scaler * BioKero H2 cost
	~	€/GJ
	~	10% of the production costs is assumed covered through coproduct selling \
		of naphtha and LPG.
	|

Methane LHV=
	55.5
	~	GJ/t
	~	https://www.engineeringtoolbox.com/fuels-higher-calorific-values-d_169.html
	|

HtJ OPEX = WITH LOOKUP (
	Time,
		( [(0,0)-(10,10)], (2019, 16.9 ), (2030, 12.7 ), (2040, 8.5 ), (2050, 7.4 )))
	~	€/MWh
	~	€/MWh of liquids/fuels
	|

BioNaphtha H2 WTP=
	(Naphtha cost - HVO Naphtha cost wo H2) / HVO Naphtha H2 cost scaler
	~	€/kg
	~		|

Grey Refinery Investment=
	refinery investment pipeline * Grey refinery investment share
	~	MT H2/Year
	~		|

refinery innovator pipeline=
	refinery continuous investment / (1-innovators) * innovators
	~	MT H2
	~		|

bioMeOH hydrogen demand=
	BioMeOH / bioMeOH H2 usage * 10^6
	~	t H2
	~	Convert from GWh to GJ, then from GJ to tons fuel, then from tons fuel to tons H2.
		Example 1:
		MeOH cons. [GWh] * 3600 [GJ/GWh] / 19.9 [GJ/t] / 15.7 [t MeOH/t H2]
		Example 2:
		NH3 cons. [GWh] * 3600 [GJ/GWh] / 18.6 [GJ/t] / 5.56 [t NH3/t H2]
	|

MeOH hydrogen demand=
	bioMeOH hydrogen demand + eMeOH hydrogen demand
	~	t H2
	~	Convert from GWh to GJ, then from GJ to tons fuel, then from tons fuel to tons H2.
		Example 1:
		MeOH cons. [GWh] * 3600 [GJ/GWh] / 19.9 [GJ/t] / 15.7 [t MeOH/t H2]
		Example 2:
		NH3 cons. [GWh] * 3600 [GJ/GWh] / 18.6 [GJ/t] / 5.56 [t NH3/t H2]
	|

eMeOH hydrogen demand=
	eMeOH / eMeOH H2 usage * 10^6
	~	t H2
	~	Convert from GWh to GJ, then from GJ to tons fuel, then from tons fuel to tons H2.
		Example 1:
		MeOH cons. [GWh] * 3600 [GJ/GWh] / 19.9 [GJ/t] / 15.7 [t MeOH/t H2]
		Example 2:
		NH3 cons. [GWh] * 3600 [GJ/GWh] / 18.6 [GJ/t] / 5.56 [t NH3/t H2]
	|

HFO IS level=
	1 / ( 1 + EXP(SLOPE * (1 - HFO IS competitiveness ) ) ) * MAX(0.1, HFO IS sector share\
		)
	* IF THEN ELSE(IS excess activity>0, 0, 1) + HFO IS competitiveness * 0.001
	~	Dmnl
	~		|

IS allocated emissions=
	Initial IS emissions * (1-SHIPPING RELATIVE EMISSIONS REDUCTION LOOKUP(Time))
	~	tCO2
	~		|

Jetfuel DA level=
	1 / ( 1 + EXP(SLOPE * (1 - Jetfuel DA competitiveness ) ) ) * MAX(0.1, Jetfuel DA sector share\
		)
	* IF THEN ELSE( DA excess activity > 0, 0, 1) + Jetfuel DA competitiveness * 0.001
	~	Dmnl
	~		|

IS excess activity=
	IS excess emissions / HFO emission factor / 3600 * Hard Regulation
	~	GWh
	~		|

BF BOF level=
	1 / ( 1 + EXP(SLOPE * (1 - BF BOF competitiveness ) ) ) * MAX(0.1, BF BOF sector share\
		)
	* IF THEN ELSE(steel excess activity > 0, 0, 1) + BF BOF competitiveness * 0.001
	~	Dmnl
	~		|

BioDiesel Cost=
	(
	(HVO Electricity Usage * GRID ELECTRICITY PRICE / 3.6 +
	(HVO Gas Usage - LPG fraction HVO) * Blue NG cost +
	HVO biomass usage * UCO PRICE +
	HVO H2 Usage * Green H2 cost / H2 LHV * 1000 / 3.6 -
	HVO Excess Heat * HEAT COST / 3.6) / HVO fraction
	+
	((HVO AF * HVO CAPEX + HVO OPEX) / HVO operating hours +
	HVO variable) / 3.6
	) * 0.95
	~	€/GJ
	~	Used cooking oil is assumed 3 times more expensive than wood per unit of energy. \
		This equals a price of UCO of around 30 €/GJ equalling market prices of \
		slightlly above 1000 €/t UCO.
		
		5% of the cost is removed through coproduct selling of naphtha.
	|

HFO DS level=
	1 / ( 1 + EXP(SLOPE * (1 - HFO DS competitiveness ) ) ) * MAX(0.1, HFO DS sector share\
		)
	* IF THEN ELSE(DS excess activity>0, 0, 1) + HFO DS competitiveness * 0.001
	~	Dmnl
	~		|

Jetfuel IA level=
	1 / ( 1 + EXP(SLOPE * (1 - Jetfuel IA competitiveness ) ) ) * MAX(0.1, Jetfuel IA sector share\
		) 
	* IF THEN ELSE(aviation excess activity > 0, 0, 1) + Jetfuel IA competitiveness * 0.001
	~	Dmnl
	~		|

NGDRI EAF level=
	1 / ( 1 + EXP(SLOPE * (1 - NGDRI EAF competitiveness ) ) ) * MAX(0.1, NGDRI EAF sector share\
		)
	* IF THEN ELSE(steel excess activity > 0, 0, 1) + NGDRI EAF competitiveness * 0.001
	~	
	~		|

Jetfuel excess share=
	MAX(0, Jetfuel IA sector share - (1-SAF min share))
	~	
	~		|

Grey NH3 level=
	1 / ( 1 + EXP(SLOPE * (1 - Grey NH3 competitiveness) ) ) * MAX(0.1, Grey NH3 sector share\
		)
	* IF THEN ELSE(fertilizer excess activity>0, 0, 1) + Grey NH3 competitiveness * 0.001
	~	Dmnl
	~		|

Fossil naphtha level=
	1 / ( 1 + EXP(SLOPE * (1 - Fossil naphtha competitiveness) ) ) * MAX(0.1, Fossil naphtha sector share\
		)
	 * IF THEN ELSE(naphtha excess activity > 0, 0, 1) + Fossil naphtha competitiveness \
		* 0.001
	~	Dmnl
	~		|

Jetfuel DA excess share=
	MAX(0, Jetfuel DA sector share - (1-SAF min share))
	~	
	~		|

DS excess activity=
	DS excess emissions / HFO emission factor / 3600 * Hard Regulation
	~	GWh
	~		|

DS allocated emissions=
	Initial DS emissions * (1 - SHIPPING RELATIVE EMISSIONS REDUCTION LOOKUP(Time))
	~	tCO2
	~		|

H2FC DS level=
	1 / ( 1 + EXP(SLOPE * (1 - H2FC DS competitiveness) ) ) * MAX(0.1, H2FC DS sector share\
		)
	+ H2FC DS competitiveness * 0.001
	~	
	~		|

H2FC DS sector share=
	H2FC DS / sum DS activity
	~	Dmnl
	~		|

HFO DS investment share=
	DS equalizer*HFO DS level
	~	Dmnl
	~		|

HFO DS sector share=
	HFO DS / sum DS activity
	~	Dmnl
	~		|

MeOH DS= INTEG (
	MeOH DS Commissioning-MeOH DS Decommissioning,
		0)
	~	GWh
	~		|

diesel price scaler= INITIAL(
	diesel price per gj / OIL PRICE)
	~	Dmnl
	~		|

MeOH DS competitiveness=
	MIN(FC ship cost / MeOH ship cost, MIN(HFO ship cost / MeOH ship cost, BE ship cost \
		/ MeOH ship cost))
	~	Dmnl
	~		|

MeOH DS Construction= INTEG (
	MeOH DS Innovators+MeOH DS Investment-MeOH DS Commissioning,
		0)
	~	GWh
	~		|

MeOH DS Decommissioning=
	MeOH DS / ship lifetime
	~	GWh/Year
	~		|

eMeOH learning=
	(MAX(eMeOH plant size, ( (MeOH DS + MeOH IS)*(1 - Green BioMeOH weight) + eMeOH
	*MeOH LHV/3.6*10^3 ) ) / eMeOH plant size) ^ ( LN(1 
	- eMeOH learning rate) / LN(2) )
	~	
	~		|

MeOH DS innovator share=
	MeOH DS inno switch / DS innovators
	~	Dmnl
	~		|

Initial DS emissions= INITIAL(
	domestic shipping emissions)
	~	tCO2
	~		|

MeOH DS Investment=
	DS investment pipeline * MeOH DS investment share
	~	GWh/Year
	~		|

Grey NG NM level=
	1 / ( 1 + EXP(SLOPE * (1 - Grey NG NM competitiveness) ) ) * MAX(0.1, Grey NM sector share\
		)
	* IF THEN ELSE(high temperature excess activity > 0, 0, 1) + Grey NG NM competitiveness\
		 * 0.001
	~	
	~		|

MeOH DS level=
	1 / ( 1 + EXP(SLOPE * (1 - MeOH DS competitiveness ) ) ) * MAX(0.1, MeOH DS sector share\
		)
	+ MeOH DS competitiveness * 0.001
	~	Dmnl
	~		|

Electric DS= INTEG (
	Electric DS Commissioning-Electric DS Decommissioning,
		0)
	~	GWh
	~		|

Electric DS Commissioning=
	Electric DS Construction / ship construction time
	~	GWh/Year
	~		|

Electric DS competitiveness=
	MIN(FC ship cost / BE ship cost, MIN(HFO ship cost / BE ship cost, MeOH ship cost / \
		BE ship cost))
	~	Dmnl
	~		|

Electric DS Construction= INTEG (
	Electric DS Innovators+Electric DS Investment-Electric DS Commissioning,
		0)
	~	GWh
	~		|

HFO DS Commissioning=
	HFO DS Construction / ship construction time
	~	GWh/Year
	~		|

HFO DS competitiveness=
	MIN(FC ship cost / HFO ship cost, MIN(BE ship cost / HFO ship cost, MeOH ship cost /\
		 HFO ship cost))
	~	Dmnl
	~		|

HFO DS Construction= INTEG (
	HFO DS Investment-HFO DS Commissioning,
		DS initial sector activity / ship lifetime * ship construction time * 1.2)
	~	GWh
	~		|

HFO DS Investment=
	DS investment pipeline * HFO DS investment share
	~	GWh/Year
	~		|

domestic shipping average cost=
	(HFO DS sector share * HFO ship cost +
	MeOH DS sector share * MeOH ship cost +
	Electric DS sector share * BE ship cost +
	H2FC DS sector share * FC ship cost) / (Yearly HFO Consumption / 1000)
	~	€/GWh
	~	€/GWh of HFO input energy equivalent. (Total operational costs, some \
		CAPEX included (not ship hull)).
	|

domestic shipping biomass demand=
	MeOH DS * bioMeOH biomass usage
	~	GWh Biomass
	~	Convert from GWh MeOH to GWh biomass
	|

MeOH DS sector share=
	MeOH DS / sum DS activity
	~	Dmnl
	~		|

LD ICE OPEX=
	LD ICE OM + LD ICE energy usage * LD fossil fuel cost
	~	€/km
	~		|

MeOH DS Commissioning=
	MeOH DS Construction / ship construction time
	~	GWh/Year
	~		|

domestic shipping emissions=
	HFO emission factor * HFO DS * 3600
	~	tCO2
	~		|

domestic shipping FC hydrogen demand=
	(H2FC DS * ICE efficiency / FC efficiency) * 3600 / H2 LHV
	~	t H2
	~		|

sum DS activity=
	HFO DS+MeOH DS+Electric DS+H2FC DS
	~	GWh
	~		|

MeOH DS inno switch=
	IF THEN ELSE(MeOH DS competitiveness > inno switch level, 1 , 0 )
	~	Dmnl
	~		|

MeOH DS Innovators=
	DS innovator pipeline * MeOH DS innovator share
	~	GWh/Year
	~		|

H2FC DS= INTEG (
	H2FC DS Commissioning-H2FC DS Decommissioning,
		0)
	~	GWh
	~		|

DS current demand=
	Fuel Use Index * DS projected demand(Time)
	~	GWh
	~		|

BioDiesel consumer price=
	BioDiesel Cost * diesel price scaler
	~	€/GJ
	~		|

H2FC DS Construction= INTEG (
	H2FC DS Innovators+H2FC DS Investment-H2FC DS Commissioning,
		0)
	~	GWh
