	~	€/km
	~		|

battery weight penalty=
	HD BE weight penalty switch * ((0.75 * 14) / (14 - HD battery weight/1000) - 1) + 1
	~	
	~	The levelized cost of trasnporting cargo with BE trucks is higher since the battery \
		weight of 8 tons removes potential cargo from the assumed 14 tons of \
		storage space. Following previously sourced material 75% of the 14 tons \
		space is utilized on average.
		
		Motivates the discussion on whether trucks and buses should be evaluated \
		on the same metrics.
	|

