Sectoral Hydrogen Demand=
	Technology Activity Levels
	~	t H2
	~	Get this from Balmorel or have a range of possible scenarios?
	|

biomass demand=
	Technology Activity Levels
	~	GWh Biomass
	~	Convert from GWh MeOH to GWh biomass
	|

sector emissions=
	Technology Activity Levels
	~	tCO2
	~		|

Yearly Ship Consumption=
	(150 * 3900 / 100 * HFO LHV) / 3600 * 365 * ICE efficiency * Fuel Use Index
	~	MWh
	~	A year of operation sailing 150 nautical miles per day.
		Converted to MWh and then converted to actual energy consumed by ship post \
		conversion losses.
		Assumptions explained in comment box.
	|

HFO capacity=
	Output energy capacity / ICE efficiency / (HFO LHV / 3.6) / 1000
	~	t HFO
	~		|

Yearly Containership Consumption=
	130 * HFO LHV / 3600 * 300 * Fuel Use Index
	~	GWh/Year
	~	Consuming 130 tons/day (Source: \
		https://transportgeography.org/contents/chapter4/transportation-and-energy/\
		fuel-consumption-containerships/). Assumes sailing 300 days of the year.
		Converted to GWh.
	|

HFO vs MeOH CAPEX=
	1.17
	~	percent
	~	According to the study, Seamaps, MeOH ships are on average 17% more \
		expensive than HFO fueled ships in capital costs.
	|

BE ship cost=
	(( OPEX electric ship + Ship battery AF ) * ( Battery capacity + Auxilliary battery capacity\
		 ) * Battery cost + 
	( OPEX electric ship + Ship engine AF ) * (Ship motor capacity * Electric motor cost\
		 + Rest of ship cost) +
	Yearly Electricity Bought * ( GRID ELECTRICITY PRICE + Charging infrastructure cost \
		* USD to EUR )) /10^6
	~	M€/Year
	~		|

HD FC energy usage=
	HD BE energy usage * HD EV efficiency / HD FCEV efficiency / H2 LHV
	~	kgH2/km
	~		|

Rest of ship cost=
	5*10^6
	~	€
	~	Own assumption
	|

HFO ship cost=
	(
	( OPEX ICE ship + Ship engine AF ) * ( Rest of ship cost + HFO capacity * Oil tank cost\
		 + Ship motor capacity * Ship ICE cost ) +
	( OPEX ICE ship + Ship battery AF ) * Auxilliary battery capacity * Battery cost +
	Yearly HFO Consumption * ( Scrubber cost + HFO cost * 3.6)
	) /10^6
	~	M€/Year
	~		|

POWER TWH=
	H2 LHV * power hydrogen demand / 10^6
	~	TWh
	~		|

H2 propulsion cost aviation=
	(Green H2 cost / (H2 LHV*3.6) ) / hydrogen fuel cell efficiency * 0 +
	Synkero propulsion cost * 2
	~	€/GJ
	~		|

TRANSPORTATION TWH=
	H2 LHV * transportation hydrogen demand / 10^6
	~	TWh
	~		|

LD FC energy usage=
	LD BE energy usage * LD EV efficiency / LD FCEV efficiency / H2 LHV
	~	kgH2/km
	~	Assumes 57% efficiency of FC car with 85% efficiency of EV car.
	|

INDUSTRY TWH=
	H2 LHV * industry hydrogen demand / 10^6
	~	TWh
	~		|

HD FCEV efficiency=
	0.57
	~	percent
	~	New assumption: Efficiency of FCEV truck is 57% like the FCEV car
		
		Builds on the assumption that the EV truck has an efficiency of 85% and \
