The amount sailed in a year assumption is based on the new electric container ships sialing between Shanghai and Nanjing (distance 150 nm/day). They have an installed battery capacity of 50MWh, but with more battery capacity at each port for recharging. Assumption is that the voided consumption is 3900 kg HFO per 100 nautical miles sailed; This is then used to convert to energy usage.|<<NnN>>||<<NnN>>|Storage needs are equivalent to the size of the batteries on the BE ship.
